WEBVTT

00:37.560 --> 00:39.440
MOMMY- COME HOME
GUZMÁN- WHERE ARE YOU?

00:56.800 --> 00:57.680
Excuse me.

00:58.040 --> 00:58.920
Darling.

01:04.520 --> 01:06.800
Everything is going to be fine. All right?

01:40.080 --> 01:42.440
All three heads
of the construction company are accused

01:42.520 --> 01:45.240
of alleged embezzlement of public funds,

01:45.320 --> 01:47.120
bribery, and criminal negligence.

01:47.560 --> 01:49.120
Shit, poor people.

01:49.200 --> 01:52.960
That's us. At least I stole to eat,
unlike these rich people.

01:53.040 --> 01:54.760
I meant their families.

01:55.720 --> 01:56.600
But, of course,

01:57.320 --> 01:59.480
you wouldn't understand that, huh?

02:00.440 --> 02:01.920
Always a mean comment.

02:03.880 --> 02:05.880
-Have you talked to Marina?
-No.

02:06.880 --> 02:10.160
You should talk to her.
She must be having a terrible time.

02:10.240 --> 02:11.240
Poor girl.

02:19.840 --> 02:20.680
-Hello.
-Hello.

02:20.760 --> 02:22.440
-Don't worry, man.
-Really, don't.

02:22.520 --> 02:23.520
It's OK.

02:24.600 --> 02:27.040
It's pre-trial detention.
We pay bail, and he's out.

02:27.480 --> 02:30.920
-And how much is it?
-Three hundred thousand.

02:32.360 --> 02:34.440
-We'll pay this afternoon.
-And the trial?

02:34.520 --> 02:36.480
It doesn't matter. They have nothing.

02:37.320 --> 02:40.640
-Then why did they accuse him?
-I don't know, Ander. Shit, I don't know!

02:40.720 --> 02:43.600
Some judge wanted to be on the news,
no fucking idea!

02:47.800 --> 02:50.400
They have nothing against him, OK?
They have no proof.

02:51.960 --> 02:53.560
That's what your dad says, Carla.

02:58.640 --> 03:00.880
Come on, we come in peace, Christian.

03:00.960 --> 03:03.320
Yeah, being called a thief
makes me feel awesome.

03:03.400 --> 03:05.800
We're saying that
if it was you who took the watches,

03:05.880 --> 03:07.000
we really don't care.

03:07.280 --> 03:09.080
Return them, and we forget about it.

03:09.160 --> 03:11.160
How can I forget
what I know nothing about?

03:14.000 --> 03:14.880
How are you?

03:16.400 --> 03:20.760
Not well, I'm not gonna lie to you.
Samuel, I don't want to talk now.

03:20.840 --> 03:24.560
Christian, we only care about one watch.
The one with a red leather strap.

03:24.640 --> 03:26.880
It was my grandfather's.
He died last Christmas.

03:26.960 --> 03:29.400
-My father is very attached to it.
-Can you listen?

03:31.760 --> 03:32.600
Yes.

03:33.520 --> 03:35.160
Sorry. Um...

03:35.600 --> 03:37.680
-Want to talk later?
-Whenever you want.

03:38.080 --> 03:40.880
If it shows up tomorrow in my desk,
we'll forget about it.

03:40.960 --> 03:42.280
Enough already. Why me?

03:42.360 --> 03:45.000
-Am I the only one who's been there?
-You're the only one--

03:45.080 --> 03:46.640
Who is penniless, right?

03:46.720 --> 03:48.920
-And that makes me a thief!
-I didn't say that.

03:50.000 --> 03:53.960
-We all know rich people don't steal.
-Christian, when did I say that?

03:59.240 --> 04:00.760
Carla, are you all right?

04:01.800 --> 04:02.640
What is it?

04:03.960 --> 04:06.440
-Your grandfather isn't dead.
-How much did you hear?

04:14.760 --> 04:18.480
All of it.
Except why that watch is so important.

04:19.360 --> 04:21.600
It's a pen drive, with documents.

04:22.400 --> 04:23.680
Don't tell your brother, OK?

04:24.560 --> 04:27.800
Papers from the business my father
and yours have.

04:28.680 --> 04:31.480
If they were to fall
into the wrong hands right now...

04:32.560 --> 04:34.360
-Stay calm, Carla--
-No.

04:57.840 --> 04:59.640
DON'T GIVE THEM THE WATCH
WITH THE RED LEATHER STRAP

05:08.040 --> 05:09.160
What are you doing?

05:10.800 --> 05:11.960
Reading comments.

05:13.240 --> 05:16.200
Babe, that's the first thing
you should stop doing. OK?

05:19.240 --> 05:20.080
Hey.

05:33.480 --> 05:34.440
What's up with you?

05:36.200 --> 05:38.840
Does your religion not allow you
to console your friends?

05:39.480 --> 05:43.200
Or maybe you can't forgive him
for sleeping with me again.

05:45.200 --> 05:46.040
Really!

05:46.600 --> 05:48.920
I don't care about what you two have.

05:49.240 --> 05:53.280
My dear...
Now that you've taken the veil off,

05:53.360 --> 05:56.680
you should consider removing
that blindfold.

05:57.080 --> 05:59.000
-Guzmán and I--
-Let's see if you get it.

05:59.240 --> 06:01.680
The only man
I'm interested in right now...

06:01.920 --> 06:03.400
is called Dostoevsky.

06:04.520 --> 06:08.480
But, of course, every time there's a man,
even if he's been dead for a century,

06:08.640 --> 06:10.920
you can't help getting in the middle, huh?

06:11.320 --> 06:14.440
He died in 1881. He's been dead 137 years.

06:15.160 --> 06:16.120
You've convinced me.

06:16.200 --> 06:18.600
It's obvious
you don't give a shit about Guzmán.

06:30.520 --> 06:32.440
OMAR, CAN YOU COME TO THE SCHOOL?

06:43.400 --> 06:44.720
Give me a moment, man.

06:49.640 --> 06:52.080
Hey! What are you doing here?

06:53.280 --> 06:54.280
Are you stupid?

06:54.360 --> 06:56.720
-Hi, by the way.
-You know who Marina's brother is?

06:56.800 --> 06:58.840
You know what he might do if he finds out?

06:58.920 --> 07:01.120
-I don't care, I need the money.
-Omar.

07:01.520 --> 07:02.840
What for? What do you want?

07:02.920 --> 07:05.880
-What do you care?
-I care about you, idiot!

07:05.960 --> 07:07.360
I don't want you to...

07:07.760 --> 07:11.720
To end up in jail or worse
for a pair of sneakers, or a motorbike.

07:11.800 --> 07:13.760
I already live in a fucking jail.

07:14.040 --> 07:15.960
This! This dough will set me free.

07:16.840 --> 07:17.960
I need it to leave home.

07:18.720 --> 07:20.040
Do you understand now?

07:20.840 --> 07:22.080
-Omar.
-Let go.

07:22.400 --> 07:23.320
Omar!

07:30.800 --> 07:31.680
Marina.

07:32.960 --> 07:34.120
I wanted to talk to you.

07:35.480 --> 07:37.200
-Sure.
-How are you?

07:37.280 --> 07:38.960
Fine. Well, better.

07:39.200 --> 07:40.080
I'm glad.

07:40.800 --> 07:43.680
I wanted to tell you that we are here
for anything you need.

07:45.560 --> 07:47.240
-Are you OK?
-Mm-hmm.

07:48.280 --> 07:51.200
Now it's exam time,
we'll do everything we can--

07:52.440 --> 07:53.280
Oh, dear!

07:54.520 --> 07:55.880
-Do you have a tissue?
-No!

08:00.400 --> 08:01.720
Open your locker, Marina.

08:08.600 --> 08:13.800
-I'll have to talk to your mother.
<i>-</i>No. She can't deal with another problem.

08:14.440 --> 08:17.040
I don't know, we've all fucked up
at some point, right?

08:17.120 --> 08:20.800
It would be a shame that for one mistake,
no matter how big,

08:21.920 --> 08:24.560
everything went to hell, right, Martín?

08:33.320 --> 08:36.960
Let's see,
Marina is an exemplary student, Azucena.

08:38.120 --> 08:40.280
And we should consider the circumstances,
right?

08:40.560 --> 08:43.880
This could stay between us.
But, it can't happen again.

08:45.320 --> 08:48.600
OK, but to ensure that,
we need to nip it in the bud.

08:49.480 --> 08:50.320
Who sold it?

08:50.680 --> 08:52.120
-What?
-Your dealer.

08:52.360 --> 08:55.280
The one who didn't hesitate
to sell drugs to a minor at school.

08:55.360 --> 08:57.880
I don't know. He never mentioned his name.

08:57.960 --> 09:00.760
You have his number in your cell.
Didn't you text him to meet?

09:03.840 --> 09:04.840
Your phone.

09:10.080 --> 09:12.200
I DIDN'T GIVE IT TO THEM

09:12.600 --> 09:14.200
-No.
-Marina, this is serious.

09:14.280 --> 09:15.440
I only need a name.

09:16.520 --> 09:18.520
Marina, give me the phone! Marina!

09:19.160 --> 09:20.800
-I can't.
-Give it to me!

09:20.880 --> 09:23.040
I'll give you a name,
but don't report him.

09:23.280 --> 09:24.360
Give me the phone.

09:24.440 --> 09:25.440
Omar!

09:27.440 --> 09:29.920
His name is Omar. He's Nadia's brother.

09:33.440 --> 09:36.360
I think this is all getting
a bit out of control.

09:36.440 --> 09:39.760
I can't have a student blackmailing me
whenever she pleases.

09:39.840 --> 09:41.560
I can't jeopardize my job.

09:41.640 --> 09:43.920
-I can't, I'm sorry.
-Of course. What a pity.

09:44.000 --> 09:47.360
Too late. The stork is on its way!

09:48.880 --> 09:51.400
Of course, you're worried about Marina.

09:51.640 --> 09:53.480
Don't worry, she will not talk.

09:53.560 --> 09:55.840
If she does,
let me remind you that you and I

09:55.920 --> 09:59.520
are on this boat together,
and would go down... together.

10:00.480 --> 10:02.360
Besides, do you think I'll let her talk?

10:06.200 --> 10:08.680
You have everything
you could wish to be happy.

10:08.760 --> 10:13.320
Why get into this mess for a shitty trophy
and a scholarship you don't need?

10:13.400 --> 10:14.280
I don't get you.

10:14.720 --> 10:16.840
Martín, do you know why I am thin?

10:18.040 --> 10:18.880
Excuse me?

10:20.240 --> 10:21.880
Because I always see myself fat.

10:22.960 --> 10:26.680
Do you know why I'm the best?
Because I'm never satisfied.

10:26.760 --> 10:30.240
You should learn to be content
with what you have to be happy.

10:30.320 --> 10:32.400
Are you happy earning €1,000 a month?

10:32.480 --> 10:34.760
Repeating the same shit
in class every day?

10:36.640 --> 10:39.120
Besides, who wants to be happy nowadays?

10:39.320 --> 10:40.640
When they can be the best.

10:41.200 --> 10:43.280
Right? Have a good day!

10:48.280 --> 10:50.760
You couldn't wait to tell me
whatever it is at home?

10:50.840 --> 10:51.920
No.

10:58.880 --> 11:01.800
Who sold you the marijuana in your room?
Was it Omar?

11:03.480 --> 11:04.320
No.

11:06.160 --> 11:07.200
It was a girl.

11:08.120 --> 11:10.920
Blonde, bleached hair. And fat.

11:12.080 --> 11:13.200
I mean, overweight.

11:14.160 --> 11:15.600
I only saw her once.

11:16.080 --> 11:17.520
Why? Is something wrong?

11:18.400 --> 11:21.440
We caught Marina with marijuana
that this Omar sold her.

11:21.680 --> 11:23.000
He's Nadia's brother.

11:25.600 --> 11:29.680
-No idea.
-Anyway, I'll have to talk to the parents.

11:37.640 --> 11:41.080
I NEED IT, IT'S IMPORTANT

11:41.600 --> 11:43.480
WHY? WHAT'S SO SPECIAL ABOUT IT?

11:43.560 --> 11:44.400
Fuck, Nano.

11:50.400 --> 11:52.040
What's going on with that watch?

11:55.720 --> 11:57.640
Thank you!

11:57.720 --> 11:59.240
Sorry I got you mixed up in this!

11:59.840 --> 12:00.920
No problem.

12:01.160 --> 12:04.080
It's no sweat off my dick
if those snobs think I'm a thief!

12:04.160 --> 12:06.360
What matters is you're out of debt.
It's over!

12:06.440 --> 12:08.280
Now you can begin to enjoy life.

12:08.840 --> 12:11.240
Working 40 hours and sweating like a pig

12:11.320 --> 12:14.160
for a shitty salary
that doesn't even cover rent.

12:14.600 --> 12:15.600
To enjoying life!

12:15.680 --> 12:17.680
No, Nano,
you and I are going to strike gold.

12:17.760 --> 12:18.960
-Really? How?
-Yes.

12:21.000 --> 12:22.600
-Hello.
-Hi.

12:22.680 --> 12:24.320
Christian, can you leave us alone?

12:24.400 --> 12:26.360
Sure,
want me to make you a sandwich?

12:26.440 --> 12:27.520
No, please leave.

12:37.760 --> 12:38.960
-Here.
-Thanks.

12:39.440 --> 12:40.400
Are you OK?

12:41.120 --> 12:43.360
Yes, but I'm a bit dizzy. It's OK.

12:47.400 --> 12:49.440
We have to figure out
how to return the watch.

12:50.600 --> 12:52.800
If it's so important,
how much would they pay for it?

12:53.240 --> 12:54.240
What?

12:54.520 --> 12:57.600
If their lives depend on that watch,
how much would they pay?

12:57.680 --> 12:58.760
That's blackmail.

12:58.840 --> 13:00.120
-Yes.
-Have you lost your mind?

13:00.200 --> 13:02.920
No, I'm using it! This can be my chance
to escape this shit.

13:03.000 --> 13:04.360
Or to go back to prison.

13:04.440 --> 13:05.720
-It's going to work.
-Sure.

13:05.800 --> 13:07.280
-Your plans never fail.
-So help.

13:07.360 --> 13:10.120
I have the balls, you the brains.
We go 50/50.

13:10.240 --> 13:12.080
We tell them if they don't pay,
we go to the press.

13:12.160 --> 13:14.160
Do you know what would happen
if those papers got published?

13:14.240 --> 13:16.200
To those rich people?

13:16.280 --> 13:18.160
-Why worry about them?
-I worry about Marina.

13:18.240 --> 13:19.120
Me, too.

13:20.760 --> 13:22.920
She's your girlfriend.
I don't want anything to happen to her.

13:23.000 --> 13:25.080
And we aren't giving
that watch to anybody.

13:25.160 --> 13:27.280
We bluff so they pay up.

13:39.880 --> 13:41.440
-Marina Nunier?
-Yes.

13:42.120 --> 13:43.120
Are you a relative?

13:43.200 --> 13:45.640
-Yes, I'm her boyfriend.
-Then you need to hear this.

13:46.240 --> 13:49.560
The tests say you are pregnant.
About four weeks.

13:51.080 --> 13:53.480
If you need anything,
I'll be in my office.

14:02.040 --> 14:03.440
It's OK, no problem.

14:03.520 --> 14:06.120
We were not together four weeks ago.
It's OK.

14:06.520 --> 14:07.400
Whose is it?

14:09.480 --> 14:10.320
Huh?

14:13.040 --> 14:15.160
Don't worry, you can tell me.
Whose is it?

14:19.160 --> 14:20.600
No, I can't, Samuel.

14:23.640 --> 14:25.400
I have to get out of here.

14:39.480 --> 14:40.320
Hey.

14:44.000 --> 14:46.480
Shit, he's not answering. He's super mad.

14:47.560 --> 14:50.480
Polo, it can't be Christian.
He wouldn't risk what he has with us

14:50.560 --> 14:52.280
for watches
when he doesn't know their value.

14:52.760 --> 14:55.560
OK, so now what? Do we apologize?

14:56.520 --> 14:58.000
It's better if you go.

14:58.160 --> 15:02.880
-He's mad at me over the photo shoot.
-And if we get him another one?

15:03.160 --> 15:05.440
-This time for real, no nonsense.
-Carla, really...

15:05.840 --> 15:07.320
Polo, we owe it to him.

15:07.400 --> 15:08.360
And you owe him.

15:09.080 --> 15:10.280
Now more than ever.

15:13.200 --> 15:14.480
How are you?

15:15.840 --> 15:17.600
-How are you, man?
-Fine.

15:18.440 --> 15:19.280
Glad to see you.

15:19.920 --> 15:22.200
I came to see if there's anything
I can do for you.

15:23.400 --> 15:25.760
-Do you have 300,000 bucks?
-Guzmán.

15:26.160 --> 15:27.000
Please.

15:27.640 --> 15:28.880
-Hi.
-Hello.

15:29.600 --> 15:30.920
We don't have the money.

15:32.800 --> 15:35.200
Not for the bail,
not for the lawyers, nothing.

15:35.280 --> 15:36.520
Our accounts are empty.

15:36.600 --> 15:39.160
We are penniless.
Dad left us with nothing.

15:39.760 --> 15:43.040
So I guess he's going to spend
the next 20 years in fucking jail.

15:43.320 --> 15:46.200
-And she's so calm, I don't get it.
-That's enough.

15:47.000 --> 15:50.600
-Why don't you ask for help at a bank?
-Nobody wants to be linked to us now.

15:51.400 --> 15:53.720
What about a friend with money?

15:55.360 --> 15:58.600
Nobody wants to call us.
Not even Carla's father.

15:59.200 --> 16:01.080
And he's Dad's partner. My godfather.

16:01.520 --> 16:02.720
And our consultant.

16:03.840 --> 16:07.400
-That's how toxic we are, Mom.
-Maybe we should call them.

16:09.240 --> 16:12.360
Marina betraying your boyfriend
can't have been nice for you.

16:12.960 --> 16:14.280
I hated her a lot for that.

16:17.640 --> 16:18.640
Because of her...

16:21.480 --> 16:23.000
Because of her, Omar and I...

16:24.720 --> 16:25.560
<i>It's about Omar.</i>

16:26.320 --> 16:28.200
I need you to say you got mixed up,

16:28.280 --> 16:31.720
that it wasn't him who sold you the pot.
I need you to talk to my mother.

16:32.720 --> 16:34.560
Ander, you know she won't buy it.

16:34.640 --> 16:36.400
-I'm really sorry.
-Yes, but--

16:37.160 --> 16:38.480
You don't know his father.

16:39.240 --> 16:41.160
-I'm sorry.
-Marina!

16:41.240 --> 16:43.200
What are you doing? Let me go.

16:46.600 --> 16:49.200
Do you want your mother to hear
about this morning?

16:52.480 --> 16:56.640
And do you want my brother to hear
why you've come this afternoon?

16:59.200 --> 17:00.240
Let go!

17:09.400 --> 17:11.760
Nadia, help us. There's a lot of work.

17:11.840 --> 17:13.840
I'm coming. I have to study.

17:14.440 --> 17:15.520
Right.

17:15.600 --> 17:16.560
Don't argue.

17:20.000 --> 17:23.360
I'M REALLY SORRY. I TRIED.

17:34.640 --> 17:35.480
Hello.

17:37.320 --> 17:38.880
Yes, Principal.

17:40.440 --> 17:41.680
Yes, of course.

17:41.760 --> 17:43.760
My husband can go tomorrow.

17:45.920 --> 17:47.080
What is it about?

17:50.520 --> 17:51.360
I see.

17:51.880 --> 17:53.040
Better in person.

17:55.800 --> 17:57.160
All right. Goodbye.

17:57.520 --> 17:58.720
What is it this time?

17:58.800 --> 18:00.600
-Did you skip class again?
-No.

18:00.680 --> 18:03.240
-Then why do I have to go tomorrow?
-Yusef.

18:04.160 --> 18:06.520
That was the principal of Nadia's school.

18:09.160 --> 18:11.120
I am as surprised as you.

18:12.120 --> 18:14.640
First the hijab.
Let's see what they come up with now.

18:22.440 --> 18:23.560
Forgive me, son.

18:24.440 --> 18:26.520
I know you are changing, maturing.

18:27.880 --> 18:30.360
I also know you are going
to make me proud.

18:30.600 --> 18:31.480
Aren't you?

18:53.240 --> 18:54.720
What are you listening to?

19:16.920 --> 19:19.200
Oh, baby, you look terrible!

19:19.640 --> 19:20.480
I know.

19:24.080 --> 19:25.480
Let me help you.

19:25.560 --> 19:28.880
I have a great product for those dreadful
dark circles under your eyes.

19:28.960 --> 19:30.880
-Leave it.
-Look at me.

19:32.080 --> 19:35.160
You know you can count on me, right?

19:35.240 --> 19:37.320
And I will not breathe a word.

19:37.400 --> 19:42.200
Really. I won't go around gossiping.
As it should be.

19:42.640 --> 19:45.120
Lu, save your breath
and ask me straight up.

19:45.800 --> 19:48.920
I told you about Martín
and my blackmail in confidence.

19:49.640 --> 19:51.800
And friends do not betray each other.

19:53.840 --> 19:55.320
We are not friends.

19:55.400 --> 19:57.200
It's in your best interest to be mine.

19:59.320 --> 20:00.160
Ready.

20:03.360 --> 20:04.360
You look better.

20:06.280 --> 20:08.480
You look prettier when you don't talk.

20:10.120 --> 20:13.000
Do you think after what he's done
I will visit him in jail?

20:16.440 --> 20:17.520
I don't know.

20:19.600 --> 20:23.400
He deserves a chance, doesn't he?
To explain himself.

20:24.520 --> 20:25.680
And he's your father.

20:26.480 --> 20:27.600
He's a thief.

20:29.280 --> 20:31.440
He even stole from his family,
so he doesn't deserve anything.

20:31.560 --> 20:34.320
What he deserves,
that's for a judge to decide.

20:35.520 --> 20:37.760
Your family should always be your support.

20:38.840 --> 20:42.280
-What is it good for, if not?
-You really think I should go?

20:43.760 --> 20:45.960
I think it's what he would do for you.

20:48.040 --> 20:49.000
Come on, Christian.

20:49.080 --> 20:52.720
It would be a photo shoot this afternoon,
same place. Polo will be with you.

20:53.320 --> 20:55.600
Of course,
to make sure I don't steal any socks.

20:55.680 --> 20:58.480
To make sure this time
there are no problems with the list.

20:58.640 --> 20:59.840
Do you forgive us?

21:03.320 --> 21:04.400
Well, let's see...

21:04.640 --> 21:06.600
when I hold the magazine,

21:06.680 --> 21:09.200
hot off the presses
and with my photo on it...

21:09.280 --> 21:10.160
maybe.

21:12.080 --> 21:14.080
